    {# NOW #}
    <div class="section-column sticky-two-rows">
        <div class="sticky-wrapper">
            <div class="sticky">
                <p class="text-extra-large">
                    The entire studio smells like fresh ink and paper, because <a href="/the-nogood-book/">The NoGood Book</a> is done! It took over 18 months to create. I redesigned it several times (read more about the process <a href="/book/closing-in/">here</a>), but it turned out exactly how I imagined it. The book is now available in the shop!
                </p>
                <div class="spacer"></div>
                <h4 class="uppercase pixel-font">Inspiration</h4>
                <p class="text-large">Found the
                    <a href="https://www.phaidon.com/en-eu/products/made-by-mschf/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MSCHF book</a>
                    in my local bookshop and immediately bought it. I knew about MSCHF because my friend <a href="https://niekdekker.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Niek</a> is part of the collective. It's beautifully designed, and one of those books that quietly raises the bar for The NoGood Book.</p>
                <div class="spacer"></div>
                <h4 class="uppercase pixel-font">Nerding out</h4>
                <p class="text-large">Moved the whole site to GitHub. Now I can clip something in Obsidian and it automatically shows up here, thumbnail and all. Next up: a bot that pushes those same clippings to Nostr and Bluesky.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="note bg-offwhite padding-small place-bottom">
            <p>Last updated {{ date | postDate }} — Inspired by
                <a href="https://nownownow.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NowNowNow</a>.
            </p>
        </div>
